    <text id="A0007T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>William H. Dunlap writes to his sister Elizabeth Reife to tell her that his
                    company will march to Harpers Ferry on Tuesday and that he may not see her
                    again. He also tells of other soldiers visits home and watch duty.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-05-12">May the 12 1861</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Dear sister</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I seat myself this morning to let you know that I am well and we were ordered
                    yesterday evening to be in <orig reg="readiness">reddyness</orig> to march to
                        <orig reg="Harpers Ferry">Harpersferry</orig> on <orig reg="Tuesday"
                    >Tusday</orig> for the purpose to be in <orig reg="readiness">reddyness</orig>
                    to take <orig reg="Harpers Ferry">harpersferry</orig> we came here on <orig
                        reg="Friday">fryday</orig> we <orig reg="have">hav</orig>
                    <orig reg="been">ban</orig>
                    <orig reg="enjoying">injoying</orig>
                    <orig reg="ourselves">our selves</orig>
                    <orig reg="very">verry</orig> well <orig reg="since">sence</orig> we <orig
                        reg="have">hav</orig>
                    <orig reg="been">ben</orig> here most all of the company is <orig reg="gone"
                    >gon</orig> home to bid <orig reg="their">there</orig> friends good <orig
                        reg="by">bye</orig> &amp; <orig reg="some">sum</orig> of the company
                        <orig reg="don't">dont</orig> mind <orig reg="it">hit</orig>
                    <orig reg="at all">atall</orig> &amp; there is not <orig reg="many"
                    >miny</orig> ever expects to see Staunton after <orig reg="Tuesday"
                    >Tusday</orig> &amp; as for my fare I never <pb n="2"/> expect to see you
                    nor <orig reg="hear">here</orig> of you <orig reg="anymore">any more</orig>
                    &amp; I <orig reg="have">hav</orig>
                    <orig reg="been">ben</orig> on guard last <orig reg="two">too</orig> nights and
                    I am so <orig reg="sleepy">sleepey</orig> that I can't <orig reg="write"
                    >wright</orig></p>

                <p>So that is all I <orig reg="have">hav</orig> to say at this time</p>

                <p>So I will <orig reg="write">wright</orig> next Sunday if I can &amp; So that
                    is all at present excuse bad <orig reg="writing">wrighting</orig> and spelling
                    So Good <orig reg="Bye">By</orig> for now and for ever</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>William. H. Dunlap</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient">To Mrs <orig reg="Elizabeth">Eliazbeth</orig>
                        Reife</name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
